  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The governing requirement mandates controlled-experiment verification of hemolysis predictions; however, the supporting validation activity was conducted as an observational study of clinical pump data rather than a purpose-designed controlled experiment. The narrative presents the observational data as fully satisfying the verification requirement, and the achieved credibility levels are reported as meeting or approaching required levels, but the structured activityType field records the true nature of the activity. Decision: Accepted.",
