      "description": "Three systematically refined hexahedral meshes (4.2 M, 11.7 M, and 31.4 M cells) were evaluated using the Grid Convergence Index (GCI) method per ASME V&V 20. GCI for NIH at the design point was 3.1%, within the 5% acceptance criterion. Richardson extrapolation confirmed monotonic convergence with observed order p = 1.93.",
